to submit a photograph when the INS document submitted does not contain one.

The 1994 proposed rule requires only the submission of the INS immigration document in whatever form that document
may be in (i.e., whether it contains a photograph or does not contain a photograph).



3. No Denial or Termination of Assistance Pending Verification Process



Three commenters asserted that the 1988 proposed rule would have implemented section 121 of IRCA ``* * *
in a manner that violates many of section 121's protections for the public, and without a well-developed plan with
